  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Project Sales Engineer",
  "description": "<p><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Identify and develop project opportunities in the marine, offshore, shipbuilding, and oil & gas\n     sectors.</li><li>Build and maintain strong relationships with shipowners, shipyards, EPC contractors, and offshore\n     operators.</li><li>Review client technical specifications, drawings, and standards for marine and offshore projects.</li><li>Prepare technical and commercial proposals, tenders, and bid documentation.</li><li>Recommend suitable equipment and systems based on class and industry standards (ABS, DNV, Lloyd’s Register, BV, etc.).</li><li>Conduct technical presentations and project meetings with clients.</li><li>Coordinate with engineering, procurement, and project teams for solution development and execution\n     alignment.</li><li>Negotiate contracts, pricing, delivery schedules, and warranty terms.</li><li>Support factory acceptance tests (FAT), site acceptance tests (SAT), and commissioning activities.</li><li>Monitor market trends, competitor activity, and upcoming offshore/marine projects.</li></ul>",
